[src:static-site-generation/elements-template] Then comes the template, which describes the structure of an HTML fragment representing a single table row.
[src:static-site-generation/elements-template] Now that the table has been created and the template defined, we use JavaScript to insert rows into the table, with each row being constructed using the template as its basis.
[src:static-site-generation/elements-template] In this example, a hidden support warning is included at the beginning of the markup.
